    rdfs:subPropertyOf d3f:accesses ;
    skos:altLabel "alters" ;
    skos:definition "x modifies y: A technique or agent x causes a digital object y to change; become different; or undertake a transformation.  Afterwards, the data or state held by a digital object is changed." ;
    skos:inScheme <https://d3fend.mitre.org/ontologies/d3fend.owl> .

d3f:owns a owl:DatatypeProperty ;
    rdfs:label "owns" ;
    rdfs:range xsd:string ;
    rdfs:seeAlso <http://wordnet-rdf.princeton.edu/id/02209474-v> ;
    rdfs:subPropertyOf d3f:associated_with ;
    skos:altLabel "possesses" ;
    skos:definition "x owns y: The subject x has ownership or possession of some object y." ;
    skos:inScheme <https://d3fend.mitre.org/ontologies/d3fend.owl> .

d3f:process_ancestor a owl:DatatypeProperty ;
    rdfs:label "process-ancestor" ;
    rdfs:range xsd:string ;
    rdfs:subPropertyOf d3f:process_property ;
    skos:definition "x process-ancestor y: The process y is a process ancestor of process x, indicating one or more process creation events were conducted were started at process y and subsequently created process x." ;
    skos:inScheme <https://d3fend.mitre.org/ontologies/d3fend.owl> .

d3f:reads a owl:DatatypeProperty ;
    rdfs:label "reads" ;
    rdfs:range xsd:string ;
    rdfs:subPropertyOf d3f:accesses ;
    skos:definition "x reads y: The subject x takes the action of reading from a digital source y to acquire data and placing it into volatile memory for processing." ;
    skos:inScheme <https://d3fend.mitre.org/ontologies/d3fend.owl> .

d3f:restricts a owl:DatatypeProperty ;
    rdfs:label "restricts" ;
    rdfs:range xsd:string ;
    rdfs:seeAlso <http://wordnet-rdf.princeton.edu/id/00234091-v> ;
    rdfs:subPropertyOf d3f:associated_with ;
    skos:definition "x restricts y: An entity x bounds the use of entity y." ;
    skos:inScheme <https://d3fend.mitre.org/ontologies/d3fend.owl> .

d3f:uses a owl:DatatypeProperty ;
    rdfs:label "uses" ;
    rdfs:range xsd:string ;
    rdfs:seeAlso <http://wordnet-rdf.princeton.edu/id/01161188-v> ;
    rdfs:subPropertyOf d3f:associated_with ;
    skos:definition "x uses y: An entity x puts into service a resource or implement y; makes y work or employ for a particular purpose or for its inherent or natural purpose." ;
    skos:inScheme <https://d3fend.mitre.org/ontologies/d3fend.owl> .

d3f:validated_by a owl:DatatypeProperty ;
    rdfs:label "validated-by" ;
    rdfs:range xsd:string ;
    rdfs:subPropertyOf d3f:associated_with ;
    skos:definition "x validated-by y: The digital artifact x has its authenticity and correctness confirmed or verified by the technique, operation, or agent y." ;
    skos:inScheme <https://d3fend.mitre.org/ontologies/d3fend.owl> .

d3f:validates a owl:DatatypeProperty ;
    rdfs:label "validates" ;
    rdfs:range xsd:string ;
    rdfs:seeAlso <http://wordnet-rdf.princeton.edu/id/00669142-v> ;
    rdfs:subPropertyOf d3f:associated_with ;
    skos:definition "x validates y: The technique x proves the digital artifact y is valid; that is, x shows or confirms the validity of y." ;
    skos:inScheme <https://d3fend.mitre.org/ontologies/d3fend.owl> .

<d3f:Reference-Remembranceofdatapassed:Astudyofdisksanitizationpractices> a owl:Class ;
    rdfs:label "Reference_Remembranceofdatapassed_Astudyofdisksanitizationpractices" ;
    rdfs:subClassOf d3f:AcademicPaperReferenceEnum,
        linkml:PermissibleValue ;
    skos:definition "Reference - Remembrance of data passed: A study of disk sanitization practices" .

d3f:AMLT0002 a owl:Class ;
    rdfs:label "AML_T0002" ;
    d3f:attack-id "AML.T0002" ;
    dcterms:title "Acquire Public AI Artifacts" ;
    rdfs:seeAlso <https://atlas.mitre.org/techniques/AML.T0002> ;
    rdfs:subClassOf d3f:ATLASResourceDevelopmentTechnique ;
    skos:altLabel "AML.T0002" ;
    skos:definition """Adversaries may search public sources, including cloud storage, public-facing services, and software or data repositories, to identify AI artifacts.
These AI artifacts may include the software stack used to train and deploy models, training and testing data, model configurations and parameters.
An adversary will be particularly interested in artifacts hosted by or associated with the victim organization as they may represent what that organization uses in a production environment.
Adversaries may identify artifact repositories via other resources associated with the victim organization (e.g. [Search Victim-Owned Websites](/techniques/AML.T0003) or [Search Open Technical Databases](/techniques/AML.T0000)).
These AI artifacts often provide adversaries with details of the AI task and approach.

AI artifacts can aid in an adversary's ability to [Create Proxy AI Model](/techniques/AML.T0005).
If these artifacts include pieces of the actual model in production, they can be used to directly [Craft Adversarial Data](/techniques/AML.T0043).
Acquiring some artifacts requires registration (providing user details such email/name), AWS keys, or written requests, and may require the adversary to [Establish Accounts](/techniques/AML.T0021).

Artifacts might be hosted on victim-controlled infrastructure, providing the victim with some information on who has accessed that data.""" ;
    skos:exactMatch d3f:AML.T0002,
        atlas:AML.T0002 ;
    skos:inScheme <https://d3fend.mitre.org/ontologies/d3fend.owl> .

d3f:AMLT0011 a owl:Class ;
    rdfs:label "AML_T0011" ;
    d3f:attack-id "AML.T0011" ;
    dcterms:title "User Execution" ;
    rdfs:seeAlso <https://atlas.mitre.org/techniques/AML.T0011> ;
    rdfs:subClassOf d3f:ATLASExecutionTechnique ;
    skos:altLabel "AML.T0011" ;
    skos:definition """An adversary may rely upon specific actions by a user in order to gain execution.
Users may inadvertently execute unsafe code introduced via [AI Supply Chain Compromise](/techniques/AML.T0010).
Users may be subjected to social engineering to get them to execute malicious code by, for example, opening a malicious document file or link.""" ;
    skos:exactMatch d3f:AML.T0011,
        atlas:AML.T0011 ;
    skos:inScheme <https://d3fend.mitre.org/ontologies/d3fend.owl> .

d3f:AMLT0080 a owl:Class ;
    rdfs:label "AML_T0080" ;
    d3f:attack-id "AML.T0080" ;
    dcterms:title "AI Agent Context Poisoning" ;
    rdfs:seeAlso <https://atlas.mitre.org/techniques/AML.T0080> ;
    rdfs:subClassOf d3f:ATLASPersistenceTechnique ;
    skos:altLabel "AML.T0080" ;
    skos:definition """Adversaries may attempt to manipulate the context used by an AI agent's large language model (LLM) to influence the responses it generates or actions it takes. This allows an adversary to persistently change the behavior of the target agent and further their goals.

Context poisoning can be accomplished by prompting the an LLM to add instructions or preferences to memory (See [Memory](/techniques/AML.T0080.000)) or by simply prompting an LLM that uses prior messages in a thread as part of its context (See [Thread](/techniques/AML.T0080.001)).""" ;
    skos:exactMatch d3f:AML.T0080,
        atlas:AML.T0080 ;
    skos:inScheme <https://d3fend.mitre.org/ontologies/d3fend.owl> .

d3f:AMLT0085 a owl:Class ;
    rdfs:label "AML_T0085" ;
    d3f:attack-id "AML.T0085" ;
    dcterms:title "Data from AI Services" ;
    rdfs:seeAlso <https://atlas.mitre.org/techniques/AML.T0085> ;
    rdfs:subClassOf d3f:ATLASCollectionTechnique ;
    skos:altLabel "AML.T0085" ;
    skos:definition """Adversaries may use their access to a victim organization's AI-enabled services to collect proprietary or otherwise sensitive information. As organizations adopt generative AI in centralized services for accessing an organization's data, such as with chat agents which can access retrieval augmented generation (RAG) databases and other data sources via tools, they become increasingly valuable targets for adversaries.

AI agents may be configured to have access to tools and data sources that are not directly accessible by users. Adversaries may abuse this to collect data that a regular user wouldn't be able to access directly.""" ;
    skos:exactMatch d3f:AML.T0085,
        atlas:AML.T0085 ;
    skos:inScheme <https://d3fend.mitre.org/ontologies/d3fend.owl> .

